\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΜΝ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">..\u003C/span>]ΥΑΤΟΝΔΕΠΟΙΚΙΛ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]IXIII[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>]ΣΟΥΣΑΠΑΝΤΟΣΚΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΜΝ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··\u003C/span>]ΥΑΤΟΝΔΕΠΟΙΚΙΛ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]IXIII[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>]ΣΟΥΣΑΠΑΝΤΟΣΚΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001179_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Copy of Gualtherus 1624 no.297 (from Arachne edition)\" src=\"ISic001179_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001179.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Copy of Gualtherus 1624 no.297 (from Arachne edition)\" src=\"ISic001179-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text after Gualtherus and Castelli\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Gualtherus records the sigmas in line 2 and the epsilon in line 1 as lunate (and he is followed by Castelli) and, assuming that this is an accurate record of what he saw, suggests a date of the imperial or late antique period. Kaibel speculated that it might be a verse text of the Byzantine period, reading τόνδε ποικίλ[ον] at the end of line 1, but despaired of interpretation. In similar vein, if correct, [-]υατον could be the end of a transliterated Latin name such as Torquatus, but the difficulty is that it is entirely possible that some of the letters are wrongly transcribed.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 143 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 297 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1753 146 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002086\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002086\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.18 no.27 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5599 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">357\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Prag and Tigano 2017 no.50 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Gualtherus records the sigmas in line 2 and the epsilon in line 1 as lunate (and he is followed by Castelli)\u003C/p> Line 1  unknown  Interlineation line 1 to 2  unknown  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[242,245,248,251,254,257,260,263],{"id":243,"html":244},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΜΝ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">..\u003C/span>]ΥΑΤΟΝΔΕΠΟΙΚΙΛ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]IXIII[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>]ΣΟΥΣΑΠΑΝΤΟΣΚΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΜΝ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··\u003C/span>]ΥΑΤΟΝΔΕΠΟΙΚΙΛ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]IXIII[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>]ΣΟΥΣΑΠΑΝΤΟΣΚΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":246,"html":247},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001179_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Copy of Gualtherus 1624 no.297 (from Arachne edition)\" src=\"ISic001179_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001179.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Copy of Gualtherus 1624 no.297 (from Arachne edition)\" src=\"ISic001179-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":249,"html":250},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text after Gualtherus and Castelli\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":252,"html":253},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":255,"html":256},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Gualtherus records the sigmas in line 2 and the epsilon in line 1 as lunate (and he is followed by Castelli) and, assuming that this is an accurate record of what he saw, suggests a date of the imperial or late antique period. Kaibel speculated that it might be a verse text of the Byzantine period, reading τόνδε ποικίλ[ον] at the end of line 1, but despaired of interpretation. In similar vein, if correct, [-]υατον could be the end of a transliterated Latin name such as Torquatus, but the difficulty is that it is entirely possible that some of the letters are wrongly transcribed.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":258,"html":259},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 143 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 297 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1753 146 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002086\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002086\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.18 no.27 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5599 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">357\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Prag and Tigano 2017 no.50 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":261,"html":262},"handnote","\u003Cp>Gualtherus records the sigmas in line 2 and the epsilon in line 1 as lunate (and he is followed by Castelli)\u003C/p> Line 1  unknown  Interlineation line 1 to 2  unknown  ",{"id":264,"html":265},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[267,269,272,273],{"html":268},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":270,"lang":107,"html":271},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΜΝ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">..\u003C/span>]ΥΑΤΟΝΔΕΠΟΙΚΙΛ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]IXIII[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>]ΣΟΥΣΑΠΑΝΤΟΣΚΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":268},{"id":274,"lang":107,"html":275},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΜΝ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··\u003C/span>]ΥΑΤΟΝΔΕΠΟΙΚΙΛ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]IXIII[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>]ΣΟΥΣΑΠΑΝΤΟΣΚΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[277,279],{"image":98,"thumb":278,"title":101},"ISic001179_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":280,"thumb":281,"title":101},"ISic001179.jpg","ISic001179-thumb.jpg",[283],{"html":55},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Fragment of a Greek inscription\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u